content: That's really helpful, thanks! I'll definitely consider those tips when designing the garden for the property on Elm Street. Since I'm planning to retire there, I want to make sure the garden is easy to maintain and enjoyable to spend time in. Speaking of retirement, I've been thinking about investing in a community-supported agriculture (CSA) program to get fresh produce delivered to my doorstep. Do you have any experience with CSAs or know anyone who's used one?
